title: Naming Rules for Coding
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

When develop codes to be distributed use the following rules:

# Start tiddler titles with this prefix: `$:/.mr/`
# Follow it with the name of your code. For example for a code called `kookma` use prfeix as `$:/.mr/kookma`
# For ''macro'' add the `macro` word after `$:/.mr/kookma` and add the name of each macro following it. For example for the macro called `mymac` its tiddler title will be: `$:/.mr/kookma/macro/mymac`
# Use the same rules for
#* ''stylesheets''
#* ''viewtemplate''
#* ''edittemplate''
#* ''pagecontrol''
#* etc...